For reporting bugs, either send a mail to one of the following email addresses
<bugs@netsniff-ng.org>, <workgroup@netsniff-ng.org>, <netsniff-ng@googlegroups.com>
or in case you own a Github account, simply visit our project's bug-tracker, which
is reachable by visiting:

  * http://bugs.netsniff-ng.org/

If you use Fedora or have a RHEL subscription, you can also report bugs (assigned
or CC'ed for <dborkman@redhat.com>) to:

  * https://bugzilla.redhat.com/

If you use Debian Linux, we also process / track bugs there:

  * http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/pkgreport.cgi?src=netsniff-ng

In any way, you'll get a reply from us.

In general, we are also highly interested in how you use the toolkit, what
problems you are trying to sovle and what kind of things you would like to have
improved. So feel free to drop us some feature requests as well.
